The paper deals with the problem of trajectory prediction in the context of autonomous driving, which is a popular research area in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of inverse optimal control (IOC) and neural networks also suggests a focus on optimization (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the problem of autonomous driving involves control systems (cs.SY) and robotics, which further supports these categories.
